I have a very simple prompt on my dev machine:<p>* I don't need the hostname. The lack of it = my machine.<p>* I don't need the username. I'm the only user.<p>* I don't need the full path. I know my machine pretty well. If I'm in doubt, pwd is half a second away.<p>* The prompt is red so I easily can scan what the output of this specific command was.<p>* Current Git-branch = helps me not make stupid mistakes.<p><pre><code>  gitprompt() {
    PS1="\[\e[0;31m\]\W$(__git_ps1 " \[\e[1;31m\](%s)") \$ \[\e[m\]"
  }
  PROMPT_COMMAND=gitprompt</code></pre>
